        <headline>Special Weather Statement issued July 9 at 7:32PM CDT by NWS Birmingham AL</headline>
        <description>At 732 PM CDT, Doppler radar was tracking a strong thunderstorm over
Bon Air, or near Childersburg, moving southeast at 15 mph.

HAZARD...Wind gusts up to 40 mph and pea size hail.

SOURCE...Radar indicated.

IMPACT...Gusty winds could knock down tree limbs and blow around
unsecured objects. Minor hail damage to vegetation is
possible.

Locations impacted include...
Sylacauga, Childersburg, Oak Grove, Bon Air, Sycamore, Sylacauga
Municipal Airport, Varnons, Overbrook, Gantts Quarry, and Mignon.
</description>
        <instruction>If outdoors, consider seeking shelter inside a building.</instruction>
